# PodPick v3 — Cursor Rules

You are working on PodPick, the internal app powering PodEngine (managed podcast pitching for bootstrapped SaaS founders).

Read CLAUDE.md at session start for full project context.

## Hard constraints

- Use Next.js 15 App Router patterns (server components default; mark client components explicitly)
- Drizzle ORM only — never raw SQL except in migrations
- Tailwind + shadcn/ui only — no other UI libraries
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any` without explicit reason in a comment
- Server actions for mutations (not API routes) unless there's a specific reason
- Anthropic SDK with model `claude-sonnet-4-5` for both pitch writer and agent

## Architectural conventions

### File organization
- App routes: `app/(public|client|va|admin)/...`
- Server actions: `app/actions/*.ts` or co-located `_actions.ts`
- DB queries: import `db` from `@/db` directly in server code
- Agent tools: `lib/agent/tools/<tool-name>.ts` (one file per tool)
- Inngest functions: `inngest/functions/<feature>.ts`
- Email templates: inline in `lib/resend.ts` (move to `lib/email-templates/` if file > 500 lines)
- Stripe handlers: `lib/stripe.ts` for shared, `app/api/stripe/webhooks/route.ts` for endpoint

### Module boundaries
- `lib/anthropic.ts` — pitch writer ONLY (single-shot generation with step parameter)
- `lib/agent/orchestrator.ts` — agent loop (multi-turn with tool use)
- `lib/unipile.ts` — Unipile API wrapper (no business logic)
- `lib/rephonic.ts` — Rephonic API wrapper with caching (no business logic)
- `lib/resend.ts` — Resend wrapper + onboarding email templates (idempotent sends)
- `inngest/functions/*` — all background jobs (no synchronous business logic here)

### Two-step pitch system rules
- `generate_pitches` REQUIRES `step` parameter — never default it silently
- Step 2 pitches REQUIRE `host_personal_context_id` — fail loudly if missing
- Validate Step 1 max 90 words / Step 2 max 110 words in `lib/anthropic.ts` validateOutput
- Never mix Step 1 and Step 2 frameworks in same generation

### Send pipeline rules
- Never bypass the Inngest send pipeline — direct Unipile calls forbidden outside `inngest/functions/send-pitches.ts`
- Day-of-week + time-of-day enforcement happens in `computeNextSendSlot` — don't replicate logic elsewhere
- Quota check ALWAYS happens at send-time (race protection), even if checked earlier

### Onboarding email rules
- Always send via `sendOnboardingEmail()` (relies on idempotency)
- Never call Resend directly for onboarding emails
- New templates require: enum addition in schema, body in resend.ts, Inngest trigger

## Forbidden patterns

- Direct fetch to Anthropic API — use `lib/anthropic.ts` or agent orchestrator
- Hardcoded Stripe price IDs — load from `env`
- Cross-client data access in non-admin routes — must filter by `client_profile_id`
- Sending pitches outside the Inngest pipeline
- Em dashes anywhere in pitch copy, marketing copy, or onboarding emails
- The word "AI" in external-facing copy (landing page, onboarding emails, dashboard help text)
- Modifying `base-prompt-v1.ts` — create v2 or v3 variants instead
- `// TODO` comments without an associated GitHub issue
- React Server Components calling client-only APIs (e.g., `localStorage`)

## Style preferences

- Direct, dense, insight-first comments — no docstring fluff
- Use `???` to mark genuine uncertainty that needs human review
- Prefer explicit names over short aliases (`clientProfile` over `cp`)
- Drizzle: prefer `db.query.<table>.findFirst()` over manually-written select-where chains
- Server components: do data loading at top of file, then return JSX

## Testing

- No unit tests required for MVP (pace > coverage)
- Integration tests for: Stripe webhook handlers, Inngest send pipeline, agent tool executor
- Manual QA checklist lives in `docs/qa-checklist.md` (created in week 10)

## Migrations

- All schema changes via Drizzle Kit (`pnpm drizzle-kit generate`)
- Never run `db push` against production
- Migration files are reviewed before merge

## Environment

- Local: `pnpm dev` + `pnpm inngest:dev` (Inngest dev server) + Supabase local or remote
- Staging: Vercel preview + Supabase staging project + Inngest cloud (preview branch)
- Production: Vercel production + Supabase production + Inngest cloud (main branch)

## When asked to do something ambiguous

Ask before implementing. Don't guess on:
- Pricing logic
- Quota math
- Email content (always check `lib/resend.ts` templates)
- Cadence rules (check `podengine-send-strategy.md`)
- Pitch copy structure (check `podengine-pitch-templates.md`)
- ICP qualification logic (check `podengine-icp-analysis.md`)

If the answer is in a doc, point me there and ask which behavior I want.
